@@ -0,0 +1,62 @@
+# Time Tracker Library Design
+
+## Architecture
+
+Single `TimeTracker` class exported from `src/index.ts`. All state management, persistence, and querying in one cohesive class. No unnecessary abstractions.
+
+## Data Model
+
+```typescript
+interface TimeEntry {
+  id: string;           // crypto.randomUUID()
+  task: string;         // Task name (unicode/emoji supported)
+  startTime: string;    // ISO 8601 timestamp
+  endTime: string | null; // null if currently running
+}
+
+interface TrackerData {
+  entries: TimeEntry[];
+}
+```
+
+## Public API
+
+```typescript
+class TimeTracker {
+  constructor(filePath: string);
+
+  // Start a named timer. Auto-stops any running timer first.
+  // Throws if task name is empty/whitespace-only.
+  start(task: string): TimeEntry;
+
+  // Stop the currently running timer.
+  // Throws if no timer is running.
+  stop(): TimeEntry;
+
+  // Get all entries, optionally filtered by date range.
+  // Filters on entry startTime falling within [from, to].
+  getEntries(options?: { from?: Date; to?: Date }): TimeEntry[];
+
+  // Get total ms per task name. Running tasks use Date.now().
+  getSummary(): Record<string, number>;
+}
+```
+
+## Persistence
+
+- JSON file at configurable path
+- Save on every mutation (start/stop) using `fs.writeFileSync`
+- Load on construction using `fs.readFileSync` (handle file-not-found gracefully)
+- Auto-create parent directories with `fs.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true })`
+- Synchronous API throughout for simplicity
+
+## Error Handling
+
+- `start("")` or `start("  ")` → throws `Error("Task name cannot be empty")`
+- `stop()` with no running timer → throws `Error("No timer is currently running")`
+- File I/O errors propagate naturally
+
+## File Structure
+
+- `src/index.ts` — TimeTracker class, TimeEntry interface, exports
+- `src/tracker.test.ts` — Tests using vitest
